Joseph Rosario Bilodeau (often misidentified as J. Rosaire Bilodeau) was a Canadian who killed six people and wounded two others in Sainte Therese de Beauport and Quebec City, Quebec, Canada on October 25, 1934, before being subdued. He was arrested, sentenced to death, and executed on June 14, 1935.
